result.execSummary:
The defendant Laura Lee Kelley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).
  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>1-5g) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)1r.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in court with attorney Patrick Howard Finlan.  Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:15 AM. State - here for sentencing as she has already plead to counts #1, #2 and #5. State has PSI and does Finlan. Finlan makes statement regarding accuracy of the complaint in regards to the speed of the vehicle, otherwise no objections. State would like to challenge Finlan's representation of the facts of the speed of the vehicle and calls Lt. Thomas Robinson. Robinson sworn in at 10:17 AM. Direct exam by State. Cross exam by Finlan at 10:21 AM. Robinson excused at 10:22 AM. State makes final argument prior to recommendation - disagrees with recommendation of PSI - recommends on count #1 - 3.5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 1.5 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES - consecutive to any other sentence that she may currently be serving, count #2 - 8 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 4 years of initial confinement followed by 4 years of ES - concurrent to count #1 but consecutive to any other sentence she is currently serving, count #5 - 8 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 4 years of initial confinement followed by 4 years of ES - concurrent to counts #1 and #2, asking that she be denied any early release programs. Finlan - jail credit of 177 days (stipulated) and will address the fact that she was not revoked on probation. Court responds. Finlan makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends a lengthy probation term and impose and stay a prison sentence of 1 year of initial confinement followed by 1 year of ES on each count, asking for 177 days jail with time served, conditions of probation would be: AODA, psychological exam/counseling, any other conditions as recommended by P&P - if releaesd today she would move to 306 North Blvd, Apt. #3, Crandon, WI . Kelley makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - 3.5 years in WI State Prison System consisitng of 1.5 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES - consecutive to any sentence she may now be currently serving (intent is that the defendant goes to prison immediately), count #2 - 8 years consiting of 4 years in and 4 years out - concurrent to count #1 but consecutive to any sentence she is currently serving, count #5 - 8 years in prison consisting of 4 years of initial confinement followed by 4 years of ES - concurrent to counts #1 and #2 but consecutive to any sentence she may currently be serving credit for 177 days. Finlan asks that the court find the defendant eligible for any programs while in prison. State responds - still objects. Court - makes her eligible for substance abuse program only and not earned release, right to appeal, costs on each count - paid thru ES, submit DNA sample, no possession of firearms, no voting rights.

Sentencing hearing at 10-19-2015 09:00 am.
Sentencing hearing at 11-18-2015 09:00 am.

Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in court with attorney Patrick Howard Finlan.  Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in custody.   Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:46 AM. State files Amended Information and Finlan is aware of it and has no objections. State - resolved - defendant would plead as followed: #1 - G as alleged, #2 - amend from original information (2nd degree as repeater 941.30(2)), #3 and #4 - DRI, #5 - G as alleged with repeater (greater than 1 and less than 5), joint recommendation of PSI with both parties free to argue. Finlan and Kelly agree. Court accepts Amended Information. Kelly pleads G to count #1 as alleged, pleads G to count #2 as amended in Amended Information, pleads G to count #5 as alleged. Court dismisses and reads in counts #4 and #5. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT. Court accepts plea, adjudges guilty, hears argument for a PSI. State makes argument for PSI. Finlan makes argument for PSI. Court will order a PSI - parties are free to argue, Finlan not sure if he will order a private PSI or not. State asking that bond be revoked and remanded to the jail until sentencing. Finlan objects to motion to revoke bond and asks for a reduction in bond to $1000.00 cash for stated reasons. State responds, objects to reduction in bond. Court revokes bond, remands to FC jail, sets for sentencing hearing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 19, 2015 at 09:00 am.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 18, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Not called on the record. Attorney Finnlan requests a short adjournment. Court reschedules to 09-02-2015 at 11:30 AM

Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in court and in custody with attorney Patrick Howard Finlan.  Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court goes over waiver and finds defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her right to a PH and finds probable cause that a felony may have been commited, binds over for trial. Proceed to ARGN - Finaln waives further reading and enters NG pleas. Bond continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for August 27, 2015 at 01:00 pm.

Attorney Mary L.R. Burns in person appearing specially - attorney Finlan has accepted case.  Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in custody/via video.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 10:07 am. Asks for PH - already read charges, penalties and rights. Bond continued.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 9, 2015 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant Laura Lee Kelley in court, in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:28 AM. Burns - SPD still cannot get attorney appointed and Burns has a conflict with the matter, asks for another week. Court continues bond, sets for AIA.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for June 24, 2015 at 10:45 am.

Defendant Laura Lee Kelley appears via video from FC jail with attorney Mary Burns appearing in person in court.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 1:29 PM. Case was scheduled for this morning, called Burn - has reviewed the complaint with defendant and found Burns has a conflict with representing Kelley. Adjourn to allow SPD to appoint different attorney. Defendant does understand charges. Bond continued.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for June 17, 2015 at 10:00 am.
